         <string>&lt;html&gt;&lt;head/&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; font-style:italic;&quot;&gt;You can open one or more parquet files and choose whether or not to group the results. To do this, the plugin doesn't use QGIS's native parquet provider; a DuckDB memory base will be created to read the parquet file(s), then the plugin's QDuckDB provider will be used to create the layer in QGIS.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
